# VS Code is pointed at this directory via --user-data-dir (see ../default.nix),
# so it writes its entire runtime profile here. Only User/settings.json and
# User/keybindings.json are tracked; ignore the runtime state VS Code generates.
# This is a best-effort denylist — fine if it misses the occasional new file.

# Caches
Cache/
CachedData/
CachedExtensionVSIXs/
CachedProfilesData/
Code Cache/
GPUCache/
DawnGraphiteCache/
DawnWebGPUCache/
blob_storage/
clp/

# Logs / crash / telemetry
logs/
*.log
Crashpad/
crashDumps/

# Per-profile / per-workspace state
User/globalStorage/
User/workspaceStorage/
User/History/
User/sync/
User/profiles/

# Backups and machine-local bits
Backups/
machineid
languagepacks.json

# Chromium/Electron storage
Local Storage/
Session Storage/
Shared Dictionary/
Service Worker/
Network/
Dictionaries/
Cookies
Cookies-journal
TransportSecurity
Preferences
QuotaManager
QuotaManager-journal
